quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,"Tâ Sîn Mīm."
  26,2,"Those are the signs of the Evident Scripture."
  26,3,"Perhaps you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are going to destroy yourself with sorrow because they do not believe?"
  26,4,"If We will, We can <span class=""h"">bestow<sup foot_note=""80715"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>upon them a sign from heaven, at which their necks would stay bent in humility."
  26,5,"But no fresh reminder comes to them from the All-Merciful but they disregard it."
  26,6,"Thus they have certainly disbelieved, but soon will come to them the tidings of what they used to ridicule."
  26,7,"Have they not seen the land— how many noble kinds of plants We have germinated therein?"
  26,8,"Indeed, in that is a sign, and in no way were most of them believers."
  26,9,"And indeed, it is your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord who is surely the Almighty, the Bestower of mercy."
  26,10,"And recall when Your Lord called to Moses, “Go to the unjust people—"
  26,11,"the people of Pharaoh. Will they never be mindful?”"
  26,12,"He said, “My Lord, I fear that they will disbelieve me."
  26,13,"<span class=""h"">And my chest tightens<sup foot_note=""80716"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>and my tongue <span class=""h"">is not fluent</span>, so send for Aaron<i class=""s"">(too) </i>."
  26,14,"And they hold<i class=""s"">(a charge of) </i>a misdeed against me, so I fear they will kill me.”"
  26,15,"He said, “By no means! So go<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>, with Our signs; We are with you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, listening."
  26,16,"So go<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>to Pharaoh and say, ‘We are indeed the Messenger of the Lord of all realms:"
  26,17,"send the Children of Israel with us.’”"
  26,18,"He said, “Did we not raise you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>among us as a child, and you stayed among us for many years of your life?"
  26,19,"And you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>committed that base deed of yours that you committed while you were one of the deniers{1}.”",footnotes:1:A denier of Pharaoh’s grace.
